docs.abstract: A Cuban immigrant, he and his brother started a tiny hardware store on the Upper East Side that grew into the sprawling Gracious Home emporium.
docs.snippet: A Cuban immigrant, he and his brother started a tiny hardware store on the Upper East Side that grew into the sprawling Gracious Home emporium.
docs.lead_paragraph: Natan Wekselbaum, who, after being slighted as a struggling English speaker by two Manhattan retailers, opened his own tiny hardware store and transformed it into an Upper East Side household goods emporium congruously named Gracious Home, died on Oct. 3 at his home in Manhattan. He was 83.

headline.main: Natan Wekselbaum, 83, Dies; Built a Cornucopia of Housewares
headline.print_headline: Natan Wekselbaum, Who Flourished With Little Hardware Store, Dies at 83
